22/03/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Bosniak deputies will initiate legal changes aimed at giving Srebrenica a special status, in light of the genocide committed there in 1995.
BiH House of People's Deputy Speaker Sulejman Tihic, who is also the leader of the Bosniak Party of Democratic Action, told reporters Wednesday (March 21st) that senior Bosniak representatives to the state, entity and Srebrenica municipal institutions have agreed to back a request to transfer jurisdiction from Republika Srpska (RS) to the state level.
Earlier this week, RS Prime Minister Milorad Dodik warned that Banja Luka would oppose any efforts to change Srebrenica's status.
(Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 22/03/07;
PBS BiH - 21/03/07)
